  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "Advanced Absolute Object Uses",
      "titleArabic": "استعمالات المفعول المطلق المتقدمة",
      "content": [
        "Beyond simple emphasis, the absolute object has advanced uses including indicating number of occurrences, type of action, and can be replaced by substitute words."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Number: ضَرَبْتُهُ ضَرْبَتَيْنِ (I hit him twice)",
        "Type: ضَرَبْتُهُ ضَرْبَ الْمُعَلِّمِ (I hit him like a teacher)",
        "Substitute words can replace the maṣdar",
        "كُلّ, بَعْض, demonstratives can deputize"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "ضَرَبْتُهُ ضَرْبًا شَدِيدًا", "english": "I hit him a severe hitting" },
        { "arabic": "فَهِمْتُهُ فَهْمًا تَامًّا", "english": "I understood it completely" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Form VIII Assimilation Rules",
      "titleArabic": "قواعد الإدغام في باب افتعل",
      "content": [
        "Form VIII (افتعل) has special assimilation rules when certain letters are the first radical. The tā' of the pattern may change to match or assimilate with the first radical."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "First radical د, ذ, ز causes tā' to become dāl: اِدَّعَى (claimed)",
        "First radical ط, ظ causes tā' to become ṭā': اِطَّلَعَ (looked into)",
        "First radical ص, ض causes tā' to become ṭā' with emphatic: اِصْطَبَرَ",
        "These changes follow phonetic harmony"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "اِدَّعَى (من دَعَا)", "english": "to claim (from 'to call')" },
        { "arabic": "اِطَّلَعَ (من طَلَعَ)", "english": "to look into (from 'to rise')" }
      ]
    }
  ],
